02:14:12.260 --> 02:14:14.700
The simple stereotyped
version of the hormones,

02:14:14.700 --> 02:14:18.760
testosterone and estrogen
are that testosterone drives

02:14:18.760 --> 02:14:21.990
libido or increases it aka sex drive,

02:14:21.990 --> 02:14:25.630
and that estrogen somehow
blunts it or is not involved

02:14:25.630 --> 02:14:26.860
in libido and sex drive.

02:14:26.860 --> 02:14:28.672
And that is simply not the case.

02:14:28.672 --> 02:14:31.850
As I describe in that
testosterone and estrogen

02:14:31.850 --> 02:14:35.060
optimization episode and
as I'll tell you now,

02:14:35.060 --> 02:14:38.850
yes, testosterone and
some of its other forms

02:14:38.850 --> 02:14:43.650
like dihydrotestosterone are
strongly related to libido

02:14:43.650 --> 02:14:46.610
and sex drive and the
pursuit and ability to mate.

02:14:46.610 --> 02:14:51.490
However, the hormone estrogen
is also strongly associated

02:14:51.490 --> 02:14:53.670
with libido and mating behavior.

02:14:53.670 --> 02:14:57.810
So much so that for people
that either chemically

02:14:57.810 --> 02:15:00.980
or for some other reason
have very low estrogen,

02:15:00.980 --> 02:15:02.970
libido can severely suffer.

02:15:02.970 --> 02:15:06.290
So it's a coordinated dance
of estrogen and testosterone

02:15:06.290 --> 02:15:10.420
in both males and females that
leads to libido or sex drive.

02:15:10.420 --> 02:15:15.420
So I absolutely want to make
clear that it's not a simple

02:15:16.060 --> 02:15:18.560
relationship between
testosterone and sex drive,

02:15:18.560 --> 02:15:19.610
or estrogen and sex drive.

02:15:19.610 --> 02:15:23.290
Both are required at appropriate ratios.

02:15:23.290 --> 02:15:28.290
Now, with that said, there are
things that can shift libido

02:15:30.440 --> 02:15:35.390
in both men and women in
the direction of more desire

02:15:35.390 --> 02:15:38.630
or more desire to mate,
either to seek mates

02:15:38.630 --> 02:15:41.750
or to mate with existing partners.

02:15:41.750 --> 02:15:44.350
And there's a quite solid literature

02:15:44.350 --> 02:15:46.750
around a few of those substances.

02:15:46.750 --> 02:15:49.600
Now, a common misconception
is that because dopamine

02:15:49.600 --> 02:15:53.640
is involved in motivation and
drive that simply increasing

02:15:53.640 --> 02:15:57.470
dopamine through any number of
different mechanisms or tools

02:15:57.470 --> 02:15:59.920
will increase libido and sex drive.

02:15:59.920 --> 02:16:02.363
And that's simply not the case either.

02:16:04.080 --> 02:16:09.080
It is true that some level
of dopamine or increase

02:16:09.290 --> 02:16:14.240
in dopamine is required
for increases in libido.

02:16:14.240 --> 02:16:16.670
However, because of
dopamine's relationship

02:16:16.670 --> 02:16:18.430
to the autonomic nervous system,

02:16:18.430 --> 02:16:21.250
and because the autonomic nervous system

02:16:21.250 --> 02:16:24.450
is so intimately
involved, no pun intended,

02:16:24.450 --> 02:16:28.810
in sexual activity in seeking
an actual mating behavior,

02:16:28.810 --> 02:16:31.780
as I described earlier,
it's actually the case that

02:16:31.780 --> 02:16:35.680
if people drive their
dopamine system too high,

02:16:35.680 --> 02:16:40.670
they will be in states of
arousal that are high enough

02:16:40.670 --> 02:16:44.430
such that they seek and
want sexual activity,

02:16:44.430 --> 02:16:47.470
but they can't actually
engage the parasympathetic arm

02:16:47.470 --> 02:16:48.940
of the autonomic nervous system sufficient

02:16:48.940 --> 02:16:51.370
to become physically aroused.

02:16:51.370 --> 02:16:54.560
There's a whole description
of this that awaits us

02:16:54.560 --> 02:16:55.580
in a future episode.

02:16:55.580 --> 02:16:58.740
But I'll summarize now
by saying for people

02:16:58.740 --> 02:17:03.040
that are taking substances just
simply to increase dopamine

02:17:04.760 --> 02:17:06.152
in order to increase libido,

02:17:06.152 --> 02:17:09.820
that can be a potentially
hazardous route to follow.

02:17:09.820 --> 02:17:13.890
Because depending on whether
or not that dopamine level

02:17:13.890 --> 02:17:18.720
is high enough that it puts
them into a mode of seeking

02:17:18.720 --> 02:17:23.110
mates or mating, but they
can't adjust their autonomic

02:17:23.110 --> 02:17:25.490
nervous system during
actual mating behavior,

02:17:25.490 --> 02:17:26.889
what essentially is I'm
saying is it can place people

02:17:26.889 --> 02:17:31.010
into a chronic pursuit but in
inability to perform sexually.

02:17:31.010 --> 02:17:33.280
And this is true for men and women.

02:17:33.280 --> 02:17:37.157
Okay, so I would just caution
people against just thinking,

02:17:37.157 --> 02:17:40.810
"Oh, a lack of libido is
simply a lack of dopamine."

02:17:40.810 --> 02:17:41.960
That is not the case.

02:17:41.960 --> 02:17:44.850
It could be from lower levels of dopamine,

02:17:44.850 --> 02:17:47.730
but it could also be for other reasons.

02:17:47.730 --> 02:17:49.877
And so these systems,
these signaling systems

02:17:49.877 --> 02:17:53.150
and these neurochemicals
are very intricate.

02:17:53.150 --> 02:17:56.850
And just simply ramping up
dopamine has actually been found,

02:17:56.850 --> 02:18:00.100
for instance, in amphetamine
and cocaine users,

02:18:00.100 --> 02:18:02.540
there's a phenomenon in which
they become hyper aroused,

02:18:02.540 --> 02:18:03.760
but can't perform sexually.

02:18:03.760 --> 02:18:06.750
This is also true for people
who take elevated levels

02:18:06.750 --> 02:18:11.080
of other recreational drugs
or who take antidepressants

02:18:11.080 --> 02:18:14.250
that increase the dopamine
system too much, right?

02:18:14.250 --> 02:18:17.060
Dosage has to be worked
out with your physician,

02:18:17.060 --> 02:18:21.050
with your psychiatrist,
such that mood is enhanced

02:18:21.050 --> 02:18:24.770
and the various aspects
of a healthy wellbeing,

02:18:24.770 --> 02:18:27.190
mind and body are enhanced,
but not so much so that

02:18:27.190 --> 02:18:31.450
that what we call the arousal
arc is locked with the seesaw

02:18:31.450 --> 02:18:34.560
in the sympathetic drive position

02:18:34.560 --> 02:18:37.610
such that sexual arousal
can't occur, okay?

02:18:37.610 --> 02:18:39.930
So this is an important point to make,

02:18:39.930 --> 02:18:41.870
because I think that a lot of people

02:18:41.870 --> 02:18:43.242
are under the impression that

02:18:43.242 --> 02:18:47.130
if they just drive up
testosterone, increase dopamine,

02:18:47.130 --> 02:18:49.280
and generally get
themselves into high states

02:18:49.280 --> 02:18:51.920
of autonomic arousal that that's
going to increase the libido.

02:18:51.920 --> 02:18:54.670
But that's simply not
the way the system works.

02:18:54.670 --> 02:18:57.610
It's that seesaw and that
seesawing back and forth

02:18:57.610 --> 02:19:01.320
that is the arc of arousal
that we talked about earlier.

02:19:01.320 --> 02:19:06.320
