02:21:47.330 --> 02:21:51.100
So there are various routes
to sexual dysfunction.

02:21:51.100 --> 02:21:55.200
The SSRIs are selective
serotonin reuptake inhibitors.

02:21:55.200 --> 02:21:57.310
They go by name brands
like Prozac and Zoloft,

02:21:57.310 --> 02:22:00.700
and there are many others now
on generic forms and so forth.

02:22:00.700 --> 02:22:03.660
Those don't always, I should point out,

02:22:03.660 --> 02:22:04.950
lead to sexual dysfunction.

02:22:04.950 --> 02:22:06.910
There's a dose dependence.

02:22:06.910 --> 02:22:10.950
Some people do quite well on
SSRIs and don't have any issues

02:22:10.950 --> 02:22:11.783
with sexual function.

02:22:11.783 --> 02:22:15.310
Other people suffer quite a
lot from sexual dysfunction

02:22:15.310 --> 02:22:18.070
while taking SSRIs, highly variable.

02:22:18.070 --> 02:22:22.870
You need to work with a physician,
a qualified psychiatrist.

02:22:22.870 --> 02:22:26.550
But nonetheless, everything
I've been saying about Maca

02:22:26.550 --> 02:22:31.080
thus far has also been
explored in the context of SSRI

02:22:31.080 --> 02:22:32.040
induced sexual dysfunction.

