02:23:17.150 --> 02:23:17.983
And they were doing this

02:23:17.983 --> 02:23:20.600
in 20 remitted depressed outpatients.

02:23:20.600 --> 02:23:21.843
So these are people that had depression,

02:23:21.843 --> 02:23:25.040
their depression was
successfully treated with SSRIs,

02:23:25.040 --> 02:23:27.860
but they were suffering from
some of these SSRI related

02:23:27.860 --> 02:23:30.170
sexual effects and Maca seemed to offset

02:23:30.170 --> 02:23:33.720
some of those effects
significantly in this population.

02:23:33.720 --> 02:23:37.970
The other studies exploring
the lack of effect on serum

02:23:37.970 --> 02:23:42.770
testosterone in adult healthy
men was a 12-week study,

02:23:42.770 --> 02:23:46.690
again, consuming anywhere
from 1.5 to three milligrams,

02:23:46.690 --> 02:23:49.130
meaning one, excuse me, 1500 milligrams

02:23:49.130 --> 02:23:51.270
to 3000 milligrams or placebo.

02:23:51.270 --> 02:23:56.270
So again, this is 1.5 up to
three grams of Maca or placebo,

02:23:56.500 --> 02:24:01.500
and they rated sexual desire,
depression, and other measures

02:24:02.500 --> 02:24:04.650
such as testosterone in the blood.

02:24:04.650 --> 02:24:08.540
Again, no change in
testosterone or estrogen

02:24:08.540 --> 02:24:11.060
estradiol levels in men treated with Maca

02:24:11.060 --> 02:24:12.580
and those treated with placebo.

02:24:12.580 --> 02:24:16.600
But nonetheless, there was a
significant and positive effect

02:24:16.600 --> 02:24:19.440
on libido with this dosage of 1.5

02:24:19.440 --> 02:24:20.877
to three grams per day of Maca.

02:24:20.877 --> 02:24:24.950
And there are several other
studies that also show this.

02:24:24.950 --> 02:24:29.370
Again, in people that taking
SSRIs and people that are not

02:24:29.370 --> 02:24:34.370
taking SSRIs, in chronically
over-trained athletes,

02:24:35.020 --> 02:24:36.220
this was also found to be the case.

02:24:36.220 --> 02:24:38.910
So seems like across the board,

02:24:38.910 --> 02:24:42.060
Maca is a fairly useful supplement

02:24:42.060 --> 02:24:44.690
for those that are seeking
to increase their libido.

02:24:44.690 --> 02:24:47.470
And there are fewer
studies involving women,

02:24:47.470 --> 02:24:51.070
but there are a few such studies
that also point to the same

02:24:51.070 --> 02:24:54.680
general positive effect on
libido in women taking Maca

02:24:54.680 --> 02:24:57.460
at equivalent doses to
those I just described.

02:24:57.460 --> 02:25:00.150
I think it's noteworthy
that Maca supplementation

02:25:00.150 --> 02:25:04.220
does not seem to adjust
testosterone or estrogen levels

02:25:04.220 --> 02:25:07.470
to any significant degree,
but it does change libido.

02:25:07.470 --> 02:25:10.350
I think that points to the
fact that there are multiple

02:25:10.350 --> 02:25:13.060
systems in the brain and
body that influence libido,

02:25:13.060 --> 02:25:15.200
not just testosterone and estrogen.

02:25:15.200 --> 02:25:16.500
And indeed we know that to be the case.

02:25:16.500 --> 02:25:21.080
Things like PEA, which is a
substance found in chocolate

02:25:21.080 --> 02:25:23.720
and is a substance that
some people supplement,

02:25:23.720 --> 02:25:27.130
is known, for instance,
to increase sexual desire,

02:25:27.130 --> 02:25:30.260
but also the perception
of sexual experiences

02:25:30.260 --> 02:25:32.700
as more stimulating for instance.

02:25:32.700 --> 02:25:34.970
So there are a lot of pathways
in the brain, in particular,

02:25:34.970 --> 02:25:38.680
in the hypothalamus, this
ancient area of our brain,

02:25:38.680 --> 02:25:42.550
that harbors neurons and
hormone secreting cells,

02:25:42.550 --> 02:25:45.850
including neurons that
can shape our perceptions

02:25:45.850 --> 02:25:49.210
of even just our tactile experience

02:25:49.210 --> 02:25:51.820
of others and their attractiveness.

02:25:51.820 --> 02:25:55.270
And indeed can shift levels
of desire, independent

02:25:55.270 --> 02:25:58.170
of changing levels of
circulating hormones.

02:25:58.170 --> 02:26:01.170
Another substance that has
been shown to increase libido

02:26:01.170 --> 02:26:04.120
across a range of human populations

02:26:04.120 --> 02:26:06.830
is so-called Tongkat Ali.

02:26:06.830 --> 02:26:09.110
I've talked a little bit about this before

02:26:09.110 --> 02:26:13.420
on the "Huberman Lab Podcast"
in reference to testosterone.

02:26:13.420 --> 02:26:15.380
And I've talked about it
extensively as a guest

02:26:15.380 --> 02:26:16.640
on other podcasts.

02:26:16.640 --> 02:26:19.143
Tongkat Ali goes by a
number of different names.

02:26:20.420 --> 02:26:22.690
One of them is exceedingly
difficult for me to pronounce.

02:26:22.690 --> 02:26:26.833
It's Eurycoma longifolia,
also called longjack.

02:26:27.860 --> 02:26:30.430
But Tongkat Ali is the typical name.

02:26:30.430 --> 02:26:32.800
This is an herb, there's
a Malaysian version

02:26:32.800 --> 02:26:34.920
and an Indonesian version.

02:26:34.920 --> 02:26:37.530
My understanding is that
the Indonesian variety

02:26:37.530 --> 02:26:40.010
of Tongkat Ali is the
one that is most potent

02:26:40.010 --> 02:26:43.063
for its effects on libido.

02:26:43.910 --> 02:26:46.320
Previously, I've talked about Tongkat Ali

02:26:46.320 --> 02:26:49.750
taken in 400 milligram per day capsules

02:26:49.750 --> 02:26:53.190
as a means to increase the amount of free,

02:26:53.190 --> 02:26:55.260
meaning unbound testosterone.

02:26:55.260 --> 02:26:58.970
So testosterone has a both
bound form and an unbound form.

02:26:58.970 --> 02:27:02.500
Very briefly, the bound
form is bound to albumin

02:27:02.500 --> 02:27:06.470
in the blood or to so-called
sex hormone binding globulin.

02:27:06.470 --> 02:27:10.650
When it's bound, it can't
be biologically active

02:27:10.650 --> 02:27:11.990
at many cells.

02:27:11.990 --> 02:27:14.220
It is important that some
of it be bound in order

02:27:14.220 --> 02:27:17.300
to get a time release
and proper distribution

02:27:17.300 --> 02:27:18.450
of testosterone through the body,

02:27:18.450 --> 02:27:21.580
but is the unbound free
testosterone that can really

02:27:21.580 --> 02:27:23.510
have its most potent effects.

02:27:23.510 --> 02:27:27.380
And there's some evidence
that Tongkat Ali can increase

02:27:27.380 --> 02:27:30.670
the amount of unbound
so-called free testosterone

02:27:30.670 --> 02:27:33.220
by lowering sex hormone binding globulin,

02:27:33.220 --> 02:27:36.310
although it is almost certain
that it has other routes

02:27:36.310 --> 02:27:38.600
of mechanism as well.

02:27:38.600 --> 02:27:42.760
Nonetheless, there are
some reports of Tongkat Ali

02:27:42.760 --> 02:27:45.110
increasing libido.

02:27:45.110 --> 02:27:49.020
One particular article,
last author, or I should say

02:27:49.020 --> 02:27:53.520
last name of first author,
excuse me, Ismail, I-S-M-A-I-L.

02:27:53.520 --> 02:27:57.710
This was published in
Evidence-Based Complementary

02:27:57.710 --> 02:28:00.210
and Alternative Medicine, it's from 2012.

02:28:00.210 --> 02:28:03.850
Reports a significant increase in libido

02:28:03.850 --> 02:28:05.170
and sexual function.

02:28:05.170 --> 02:28:07.950
There are other studies,
not a lot of them,

02:28:07.950 --> 02:28:12.540
not as many robust, controlled,
quality peer-reviewed

02:28:12.540 --> 02:28:14.170
studies as there are from Maca.

02:28:14.170 --> 02:28:17.550
Nonetheless, a number of people,
men and women that I know

02:28:17.550 --> 02:28:21.220
do take Tongkat Ali and it
seems to work well for them.

02:28:21.220 --> 02:28:22.960
The question always comes up around

02:28:22.960 --> 02:28:23.920
discussion of supplements.

02:28:23.920 --> 02:28:25.460
Do you need to cycle these things?

02:28:25.460 --> 02:28:27.230
The only way to determine that is really

02:28:27.230 --> 02:28:29.960
to do your blood work,
monitor liver enzymes,

02:28:29.960 --> 02:28:32.210
monitor hormone levels and so forth.

02:28:32.210 --> 02:28:35.160
So I simply can't say
whether or not you need to,

02:28:35.160 --> 02:28:36.355
or you don't need to cycle them.

02:28:36.355 --> 02:28:40.970
Typically Tongkat Ali
and Maca are not cycled

02:28:40.970 --> 02:28:43.640
in any regular kind of
way that I'm aware of.

02:28:43.640 --> 02:28:46.330
But again, you really need
to check with your doctor

02:28:46.330 --> 02:28:49.260
if you're going to initiate
taking any of these things.

02:28:49.260 --> 02:28:51.440
And you certainly should
do your best to monitor

02:28:51.440 --> 02:28:54.330
your blood work as well as
subjective measures in evaluating

02:28:54.330 --> 02:28:55.460
whether or not they're working for you,

02:28:55.460 --> 02:28:56.770
safe for you and so forth.

02:28:56.770 --> 02:28:59.320
The third and final substance/supplement

02:28:59.320 --> 02:29:02.000
that I want to touch on
as it relates to libido

02:29:02.000 --> 02:29:03.763
is called Tribulus Terrestris.

02:29:04.770 --> 02:29:09.770
So that's T-R-I-B-U-L-U-S,
terrestris, T-E-R-R-E-S-T-R-I-S.

02:29:12.410 --> 02:29:16.390
This is a commonly sold
over-the-counter supplement

02:29:16.390 --> 02:29:19.020
for increasing testosterone,

02:29:19.020 --> 02:29:22.620
for fitness purposes and so on.

02:29:22.620 --> 02:29:24.690
Whether or not it actually does that

02:29:24.690 --> 02:29:27.710
to a meaningful degree, isn't clear.

02:29:27.710 --> 02:29:31.200
But I'm aware of four
peer-reviewed studies

02:29:32.100 --> 02:29:36.760
that were focused on
both males and females

02:29:36.760 --> 02:29:39.840
ranging anywhere from 18 years old

02:29:39.840 --> 02:29:42.130
all the way up to 65 plus.

02:29:42.130 --> 02:29:43.250
They say 65 plus.

02:29:43.250 --> 02:29:45.090
I guess it could be 70, it could be 80.

02:29:45.090 --> 02:29:45.923
I don't know.

02:29:45.923 --> 02:29:50.670
But a fairly broad age range
where people took anywhere

02:29:50.670 --> 02:29:55.670
from 750 milligrams per day
divided into three equal doses.

02:29:57.430 --> 02:30:01.370
So 750 total per day divided
into three equal doses

02:30:01.370 --> 02:30:05.440
of Tribulus or placebo for 120 days.

02:30:05.440 --> 02:30:08.750
This particular study
was focused on females.

02:30:08.750 --> 02:30:11.590
And according to the female
sexual function index

02:30:11.590 --> 02:30:13.980
questionnaire, no significant difference

02:30:13.980 --> 02:30:18.540
between any of the groups,
however free and bio-available

02:30:18.540 --> 02:30:19.820
testosterone increased in the group taking

02:30:19.820 --> 02:30:23.270
Tribulus Terrestris, total testosterone

02:30:23.270 --> 02:30:25.290
did not reach statistical significance.

02:30:25.290 --> 02:30:28.460
So this is the inverse
of what we see with Maca,

02:30:28.460 --> 02:30:31.160
where there do seem to be
increases in testosterone,

02:30:31.160 --> 02:30:34.760
which would predict that there
would be increase in libido.

02:30:34.760 --> 02:30:37.930
In this case, this was
postmenopausal women,

02:30:37.930 --> 02:30:39.240
there was no increase in libido.

02:30:39.240 --> 02:30:41.150
There was an increase in testosterone.

02:30:41.150 --> 02:30:43.700
I mentioned it only because
there might be instances

02:30:43.700 --> 02:30:47.770
in which people want to
increase their testosterone.

02:30:47.770 --> 02:30:50.250
It does seem that Tribulus,
at least in that population

02:30:50.250 --> 02:30:51.860
is capable of doing that.

02:30:51.860 --> 02:30:54.470
Now there's a separate
study that was done,

02:30:54.470 --> 02:30:58.440
a double-blind study lasting
anywhere from one to six months

02:30:58.440 --> 02:31:02.350
that had a clear and
significant increase in libido.

02:31:02.350 --> 02:31:05.080
Now this was taking six grams.

02:31:05.080 --> 02:31:09.350
So that's 6,000 milligrams
of Tribulus root for 60 days.

02:31:09.350 --> 02:31:11.740
And it did seem to
increase various aspects

02:31:11.740 --> 02:31:12.893
of sexual function.

02:31:13.950 --> 02:31:18.600
And there was what appeared
to be a substantial 16.3%

02:31:18.600 --> 02:31:21.800
increase in testosterone,
but in this particular study

02:31:21.800 --> 02:31:24.670
because of the variability
across individuals

02:31:24.670 --> 02:31:27.620
that did not actually arrive
at statistical significance.

02:31:27.620 --> 02:31:30.738
Now, there were a number of
other studies that explored

02:31:30.738 --> 02:31:34.670
the role of Tribulus, in
particular, in females.

02:31:34.670 --> 02:31:37.660
And one of those studies was a study

02:31:37.660 --> 02:31:40.710
that was actually quite short,
it was two to four weeks.

02:31:40.710 --> 02:31:43.070
It involved 67 subjects.

02:31:43.070 --> 02:31:46.530
These were subjects that had
experienced a loss of libido

02:31:46.530 --> 02:31:50.070
and took Tribulus divided
into two equal doses,

02:31:50.070 --> 02:31:51.640
compared that to placebo.

02:31:51.640 --> 02:31:56.130
And they did see a significant
improvement in these measures

02:31:56.130 --> 02:31:58.070
of sexual desire and function

02:31:58.070 --> 02:32:00.440
on this female sexual function index.

02:32:00.440 --> 02:32:03.210
So there is some evidence
that Tribulus can be effective

02:32:03.210 --> 02:32:06.110
in increasing testosterone
in certain populations,

02:32:06.110 --> 02:32:08.790
in increasing sexual desire and function

02:32:08.790 --> 02:32:12.030
in certain populations
in particular in females.

02:32:12.030 --> 02:32:13.950
I think more studies are certainly needed.

02:32:13.950 --> 02:32:17.910
But these three substances/supplements,

02:32:17.910 --> 02:32:22.600
Maca, Tongkat Ali, in particular,
Indonesian Tongkat Ali,

02:32:22.600 --> 02:32:26.260
